Since they made changes to one of my sibling's favorite foods (muffins), I thought it best that I learn how to bake and use some of all that good stuff I forage up.  My sister is always complaining that she is eating those veggies and muffins up so quickly.<br>
I did manage to make a rat kabob last night.  Even though the item said it would add +1 DEX and +1 AGI, we did not notice any increase when the item was eaten.  (My thanks to Nine for being my guinea pig.)  <br>
***********************************************************<br>
** NOTE **: just read a post after writing this. The item must be eaten normally and not right-clicked.  Also, if you right-click to eat it, the effect of having eaten something will only last half as long.<br>
***********************************************************<br>
I have discovered that if I &quot;force eat&quot; some normal food by right-clicking on it, I still get the benefits of the stat food in my top inventory slot without consuming it, because I'm &quot;not hungry&quot;. =P<br>
<br>
~~ Galadhriel <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugaladhriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadhriel</A> at: 6/18/01 1:18:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugaladhriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadhriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 1:08:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Durations of Food</span><hr size=1> from Eqtraders.com message boards:<br>
