<br>
Cashew and Co. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugaladhriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadhriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/01 9:56:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skewers and Pots and things...</span><hr size=1> When I attempted to make Rat Kabobs, my skewers were returned to me upon successes and failures.  I haven't tried to make anything using my pot (crafted by Nine also) yet, as my skill is not high enough yet.<br>
I do not know if you could eventually lose your skewers and pot like a fishing pole, but I'm sure Nine would be more than happy to make more once I make him some more metal bits.<br>
Turns on the oven for another round of baking....<br>
~~ Galadhriel<br>
<br>
P.S. There are actually recipes out there for items that give WIS and INT bonuses - mainly cannibalistic ones like Blackened Tier'dal with +1 DEX, +2 INT, +1 AGI (grins slyly at the Dark Elves in the guild) or even &lt;gulp&gt; Elven Veal which has +1 DEX/WIS/AGI/INT or Smoked Wood Elf with +2 WIS/AGI. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugaladhriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadhriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/2/01 11:53:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skewers and Pots and things...</span><hr size=1> I have since made rabbit stew (a hearty meal) and the pot is returned on successes and failures.  Thanks to Fromunder's soloing efforts in Everfrost, I was able to make a stack of mammoth steaks and beer braised mammoth steaks for Fromunder and Melwyn.  These items add nice STR bonuses and are light in addition to being banquet sized.  I think I may have to spend some time in Eastern Wastes hunting mammoths for more.  According to Fromunder and Ziag, the mammoths are being hunted by so many in Everfrost that they are getting hard to find!<br>
Compared to the other trades, baking is a relatively inexpensive trade to learn.  You might need sauces, spices or flasks of water, but some of the useful food recipes do not require very expensive components.  And of course, Nine can make you any pie tins, skewers, or pots you might need.  I always need the practice making metal bits for him!  I encourage all the foragers in the guild to take up this trade.<br>
Oh, and I foraged up Surefall Sap in Qeynos Hills the other day and it is a Refreshing Drink!<br>
Well, back to organizing my recipe cards.....Gala <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugaladhriel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galadhriel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/01 12:02:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ** Drinks **</span><hr size=1> I read on the Eqtraders.com Baking message board that you can buy JumJum juice for abour 3 or 4 sp each vs the gp that the hair tonic outside Freeport costs. <br>
<br>
I have a self only port to Misty Thicket and will venture over there to investigate.<br>
** Update **  The jumjum juice is sold by Daleen Leafsway by the druid guild in Rivervale.  It is a refreshing drink and cost me 5gp 4sp for a stack of 20 with 98 Charisma.<br>
